en: Harvard 1960.339
collection_history

Formerly in the collection of the Princess Tricase; later in the Garrett Chatfield Pier collection; purchased in sale of the latter in New York (American Art Association, Anderson Galleries, March 6-7, 1936, no. 4239).
condit

Unbroken. The surface in worn and abraded in several places, particularly on Nereus and the Nereid on side A, and the black glaze on side B, the foot, handle B/A, and beneath handle A/B. Irregular stain marks and discoloration in the figure scenes were caused by the removal of incrustation.
